      "identifier": "ea:concept:ontology",
      "name": "Ontology",
      "abstract": "Ontologies make domain meaning explicit and interoperable, while taxonomies organize concepts primarily through classification and hierarchy.",
      "description": "In knowledge engineering, an ontology is an explicit specification of the kinds of entities, properties, relationships and constraints used to represent a domain.",
